stylometry: Aggregate Planning helps to find the best optimal solution in a workplace in a certain amount of time.  Factors that need to be considered in aggregate planning would be the time that it needs to be completed by.  This is important to not miss deadlines.  The goal ultimiately is to get the aggregate planning done in the desired time.  There are tradeoffs involved, and that would be money.  Ideally the cost would be minimized, but it is a tradeoff.  Another trade-off would be labor, if a company is pushing to meet a deadline, labor will need to be increased.
